Sentencas: Investigation of the manufacturing process of anode-electrolyte substrate (half-cell) is of paramount importance for improving the electrodes of solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Effects of via hot-pressing loads and co-sintering temperature on anode-electrolyte substrate expansion in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, the effects of hot-pressing loads and co-sintering temperatures on the anode-electrolyte substrate were examined.
Titulo: Effects of via hot-pressing loads and co-sintering temperature on anode-electrolyte substrate expansion in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Loads of 2000, 2500, 3000, and 3500 PSI were applied during the hot-pressing process.
Titulo: Effects of via hot-pressing loads and co-sintering temperature on anode-electrolyte substrate expansion in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After via hot pressing, the anode-electrolyte substrates were co-sintered at temperatures of 1300, 1350, 1400, and 1450 degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of via hot-pressing loads and co-sintering temperature on anode-electrolyte substrate expansion in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, SEM was used to investigate the structure of the anode-electrolyte substrates after via hot pressing and co-sintering.
Titulo: Effects of via hot-pressing loads and co-sintering temperature on anode-electrolyte substrate expansion in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that at hot-pressing loads of 3000 and 3500 PSI, the shape, dimension, and quality of the anode-electrolyte substrates were better than those in the other cases.
Titulo: Effects of via hot-pressing loads and co-sintering temperature on anode-electrolyte substrate expansion in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the results show that the structure of cell with co-sintering temperatures of 1300 and 1350 degrees C were much lower than those with temperatures of 1400 and 1450 degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of via hot-pressing loads and co-sintering temperature on anode-electrolyte substrate expansion in solid oxide fuel cells
